spirit:component.spirit:description: The 10 Gigabit Ethernet Media Access Controller (XGMAC) LogiCORE is designed to the IEEE 802.3 standard specification to provide up to 10 gigabits per second (Gbps) total bandwidth. The core supports LAN/WAN mode operation and it provides support for VLAN and JUMBO frames. It also provides optional network management features including statistics gathering and flow control. The core can be configured and monitored through a AXI4-Lite interface. In addition, the core is designed to seamlessly connect to the XAUI LogiCORE, RXAUI LogiCore and the 10-Gigabit Ethernet PCS/PMA LogiCORE (providing 10GBASE-R or 10GBASE-KR standards) via the cores XGMII interface.
